dct_title_s: [Geological Survey of England and Wales : one inch to the mile map. New Series.] Berwick upon Tweed, drift, sheet 2
dct_description_sm: Great Britain. Ordnance Survey of England. (Third edition) Great Britain. Geological Survey of England and Wales. Sheet 2 drift. Geological Survey of Great Britain. North Decimal Degree 55.866700. South Decimal Degree 55.7000. East Decimal Degree -1.5500. West Decimal Degree -2.0167. In upper left margin: Ordnance Survey of England (Third edition). Relief shown by contour interval and spot heights. Depths shown by contour interval. Transverse Mercator projection. National grid system. "Published on sheets. England 110 N.E. (Old series) in 1884, Scotland 26 in 1883 & 34 in 1863. Revised in 1921-22.".
dct_publisher_sm: [Southampton ; Chessington, Surrey] : Director General, Ordnance Survey, 1926.
